main event: An unidentified elliptical object resembling a jet aircraft was seen flying at high speed above St. Paul, Minnesota on August 9, 1952.
interesting points: The object moved from southeast to northwest before disappearing abruptly.,Witnesses reported a clear blue sky and calm weather conditions during the sighting.,The object was described as being silver or aluminum in color.,Observers noted that the object made no sound during its flight.,The length of observation was approximately 10 to 15 seconds.
witness description: A civilian observer outside his home observed the object in the clear sky.
